one_reviews_text:
{you can check out the playthrough list on my youtube channel Greg Sallans}
I remember when Star Trek Bridge Crew first came out I was so excited.  Being a life long Trekkie the thought of being able to live in the trek world in VR was a dream come true.  It was a fantastic game and a super fun experience playing with other trekkies but it seemed like they missed so much opportunity.  Why couldn't we roam the ship, or fight off invaders, or teleport to other ships or,. get up from our seats at least??  After a couple times of playing it I just didn't feel like it anymore.   

Enter From Other Suns.  EVERYTHING I wanted to do in bridge crew.   It was so fun being able to run to areas of your ship and fix things if the needed repair and your crew mates were busy fixing other things.  The interface was way more fun to operate.  Especially for the engineering part.  Being able to teleport to other ships and battle the inhabitants and loot their cargo holds was a blast!  And then, to my surprise, I started hearing people talking,. and then actually responding to me, and the next thing I knew I had a crew!  If there is one thing I usually stray away from it's multiplayer on line with strangers.  But in the VR communtiy when I have gone out of my comfort zone and done this I have never regretted it.  I was joined by CONTARII and QUATERNIONPIPELINE and holy cow did we have fun.  At least I did. haha!  Everything ran super smooth, and lightning fast.  The gun upgrades, shields, health system,,. just everything is great in this game.  If you felt a bit let down by Bridge Crew you should def pick this one up!  maybe we'll see eachother in the metaverse!
